<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900426-0108</DOCNO><DOCID>900426-0108.</DOCID><HL>   Ameritrust Corp. Posts Loss</HL><DATE>04/26/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   AMTR</CO><IN>BANKS (BNK)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   CLEVELAND -- Ameritrust Corp. had a loss of $51.6 millionin the first quarter, as the bank holding company took a hugeprovision to comply with tougher regulatory standards. In theyear-ago first quarter, Ameritrust earned $27.8 million, or76 cents a share.   In the quarter just ended, Ameritrust increased itsloan-loss provision by $120 million after federal examinersreviewed the company's loan portfolio. Ameritrust saidexaminers expressed concern over the company's commercialreal-estate loans and highly leveraged transactions. Thebank's nonperforming assets increased to $240.8 million from$214.3 million at the end of 1989.</LP><TEXT>   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Ameritrustclosed at $18.125, unchanged.</TEXT></DOC>